  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <p><strong>Will using online therapy affect my academic record or any future applications?</strong></p>
  <p>No. Private online therapy is completely separate from your university. Your therapist is not affiliated with the university and has no obligation to report to them. What you discuss in therapy is confidential.</p>
  <p><strong>My university has free counseling — should I use that instead?</strong></p>
  <p>Free campus counseling is valuable and you should use it if it's accessible. If the wait time is too long, session limits apply, or you'd prefer more privacy, online therapy is an excellent alternative or supplement.</p>
  <p><strong>Can I use therapy during exams period?</strong></p>
  <p>Yes — and this is often when it's most valuable. Many therapists can accommodate irregular scheduling during exam periods. The support is particularly useful when academic stress peaks.</p>
  <p><strong>What if I move between cities for study or internships?</strong></p>
  <p>Online therapy continues uninterrupted regardless of your physical location. Your therapist stays with you whether you're at your university, home for break, or on a summer internship.</p>
